Senate Resolution 512
By: Senator James of the 28th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Juneteenth Atlanta upon its 13th Annual Parade & Music
2 Festival; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, one of the largest and most impactful Juneteenth celebrations in the world,
4 Juneteenth Atlanta has grown from its humble beginnings into an expansive cultural
5 movement that unites communities across the African diaspora; and
6 WHEREAS, the 13th Annual Juneteenth Atlanta Parade & Music Festival, to be held June
7 14-15, 2025, at Piedmont Park, will feature the themes "Reparations Over Everything" and
8 "True Identity = True Freedom"; and
9 WHEREAS, since its inception, Juneteenth Atlanta has remained committed to
10 commemorating emancipation and empowering communities through events such as the
11 Juneteenth Black History Parade, family reunions, cultural markets, and healing circles; and
12 WHEREAS, during the height of the COVID-19 pandemic in 2020, Juneteenth Atlanta led
13 a powerful rally alongside community leaders and 10,000 participants to sustain unity and
14 recognition during a time of national uncertainty, and in 2021, they overcame extreme
