15 logistical challenges to host a record-breaking event with over 250 vendors and more than
16 2,200 parade participants; and
17 WHEREAS, the 2022 and 2023 Juneteenth Atlanta Parade & Music Festivals featured
18 expansive cultural programming and major headline performances, with the 2023 festival
19 attracting over 100,000 attendees and introducing additions such as a wrestling showcase,
20 karaoke stage, and enhanced stage production; and
21 WHEREAS, Juneteenth Atlanta was invited by the National Juneteenth Observance
22 Foundation to the White House on June 19, 2024, where Georgia participants performed on
23 the White House lawn and led a celebratory parade through national monuments; and
24 WHEREAS, Juneteenth Atlanta remains a powerful nonprofit voice for justice, education,
25 cultural pride, and reunification across the African diaspora, partnering with communities
26 from across the southern United States, the Caribbean, and the African continent in pursuit
27 of shared liberation and celebration.
28 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
29 recognize and commend Juneteenth Atlanta upon its 13th Annual Parade & Music Festival
30 for its historic and ongoing contributions to cultural awareness, unity, and justice as well as
31 extend their best wishes for a successful event.
32 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
33 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Juneteenth
34 Atlanta.
